== 經歷 ==
保羅·杜洛夫出生於[[苏联|苏联]][[俄罗斯苏维埃联邦社会主义共和国|俄罗斯]][[圣彼得堡|列宁格勒]]（今[[俄罗斯|俄罗斯]][[圣彼得堡|圣彼得堡]]），但在[[意大利|意大利]][[都灵|都灵]]度過童年。他的父親瓦列里（該擁有語言學[[博士|博士]]之學位）受僱於此地。他就讀一所[[意大利|意大利]]的小學，返回[[俄罗斯|俄罗斯]]後，就讀了[[圣彼得堡国立大学|圣彼得堡国立大学]]語言學院<ref>{{cite web|last=Pigareva|first=Olga|title=Prominent Russians: Pavel Durov|url=http://russiapedia.rt.com/prominent-russians/science-and-technology/pavel-durov/|publisher=Russia Today|accessdate=8 March 2013|archive-date=2013-03-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130306023252/http://russiapedia.rt.com/prominent-russians/science-and-technology/pavel-durov/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2006年，他从圣彼得堡国立大学毕业。杜洛夫早年的经历和事业在俄语出版的图书《The Durov Code. The True Story of VK and its Creator》中有描述。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Код Павла Дурова: пять историй из жизни «ВКонтакте» и ее создателя {{!}} Бизнес|url=https://www.forbes.ru/sobytiya-opinion/lyudi/212150-kod-pavla-durova-pyat-istorii-iz-zhizni-vkontakte-i-ee-sozdatelya|accessdate=2020-06-25|date=2012-11-22|work=Forbes.ru|language=en-US|archive-date=2020-06-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200601204115/https://www.forbes.ru/sobytiya-opinion/lyudi/212150-kod-pavla-durova-pyat-istorii-iz-zhizni-vkontakte-i-ee-sozdatelya|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在2006年，杜洛夫受到Facebook启发创立 [[VKontakte|VKontakte]]<ref>{{Cite news|title=Once Celebrated in Russia, the Programmer Pavel Durov Chooses Exile|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/03/technology/once-celebrated-in-russia-programmer-pavel-durov-chooses-exile.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2014-12-02|accessdate=2020-06-25|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Danny|last=Hakim|archive-date=2019-05-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190518203152/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/03/technology/once-celebrated-in-russia-programmer-pavel-durov-chooses-exile.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，在这个期间，他和他的哥哥尼古拉从无到有一手建立VKontakte网站，并将VKontakte带领到大约30亿的估值。<ref name="#2"/>

杜洛夫在經濟和政治上是[[自由意志主義|自由意志主義]]者，此外他[[素食|茹素]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://vk.com/id1 |title=Pavel's vk.com profile |accessdate=2014-02-22 |archive-date=2017-02-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170216122216/https://vk.com/id1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他出版了無政府資本主義的宣言，描述自己對改善[[俄罗斯|俄罗斯]]的想法<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.afisha.ru/article/pavel-durov-VKontakte/ |title=www.afisha.ru |accessdate=2017-10-31 |archive-date=2012-11-20 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6CJjFArA2?url=http://www.afisha.ru/article/pavel-durov-vkontakte/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在他的27歲生日，他捐下一百萬[[美元|美元]]給[[維基媒體基金會|維基媒體基金會]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://venturebeat.com/2012/01/24/durov-wikipedia-donation/ |title=venturebeat.com |accessdate=2014-02-22 |archive-date=2012-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120722220026/http://venturebeat.com/2012/01/24/durov-wikipedia-donation/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Founder of Facebook for Russia donates $1M to Wikipedia at DLD|url=https://venturebeat.com/2012/01/24/durov-wikipedia-donation/|accessdate=2020-06-25|date=2012-01-24|work=VentureBeat|language=en-US|archive-date=2012-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120722220026/http://venturebeat.com/2012/01/24/durov-wikipedia-donation/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=In Conversation (Jimmy Wales, Founder of Wikipedia & Pavel Durov) {{!}} DLD12|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hEHd4HbOLYM|accessdate=2020-06-25|language=zh-CN|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125062822/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hEHd4HbOLYM|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2014年4月1日愚人節當天辭去[[VKontakte|VKontakte]][[執行長|執行長]]一職，在2天後證實這是惡作劇<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.peeep.us/613359bf |title=Запись на стене Павла Дурова |access-date=2014-04-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140407112606/http://www.peeep.us/613359bf |archive-date=2014-04-07 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。2014年4月21日，[[VKontakte|VKontakte]]公司宣布他已不再擔任執行長職位，背後的原因據推測可能是俄羅斯政府想要掌握VK社群網站故架空其公司職位，為此保羅也決定離開俄羅斯另行創業<ref>{{cite news|title=VKontakte Founder Pavel Durov Learns He's Been Fired Through Media|url=http://www.themoscowtimes.com/business/article/VKontakte-founder-pavel-durov-learns-hes-been-fired-through-media/498641.html|accessdate=2014-05-11|newspaper=The Moscow Times|date=2014-04-22|language=en|archive-date=2014-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425075542/http://www.themoscowtimes.com/business/article/vkontakte-founder-pavel-durov-learns-hes-been-fired-through-media/498641.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Pavel Durov left Russia after being pushed out |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2014-04-22/news/49318882_1_social-network-VKontakte-pavel-durov-founder-mark-zuckerberg |accessdate=2014-05-11 |newspaper=The Economic Times |date=2014-04-22 |language=en |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140426111428/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2014-04-22/news/49318882_1_social-network-vkontakte-pavel-durov-founder-mark-zuckerberg |archivedate=2014-04-26 }}</ref>。

